{"questionId":"9073363","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A Σ<sup>+</sup> particle decays from rest into a neutron and another particle X according to the reaction</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Σ<sup>+</sup> → n + X</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The following data are available.</span></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Rest mass of Σ<sup>+</sup> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = 1190 MeV c<sup>–2</sup><br>Momentum of neutron &nbsp;&nbsp; = 185 MeV c<sup>–1</sup></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Calculate, for the neutron,</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">the total energy.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">neutron energy&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>185</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>940</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>958</mn></math> «MeV» ✔<br></span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NOTE: Allow 1.5 × 10<sup>–10</sup> «J»</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073363","referenceCode":"19N.3.HL.TZ0.a(i)","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"the total energy.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Additional higher level option topics)","A.4 – Relativistic mechanics (HL only)","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Additional higher level option topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}